# @narai/{{SERVICE_SLUG}}-agent-connector

{{DESCRIPTION}} Ships a JSON-envelope CLI and a library API.

## Install

```bash
npm install @narai/{{SERVICE_SLUG}}-agent-connector
export {{SERVICE_SLUG_UPPER}}_TOKEN="..."
```

Node 20+. {{CREDENTIAL_NOTE}}

## CLI

```bash
npx {{SERVICE_SLUG}}-agent-connector --action <name> --params '<json>'
```

### Supported actions

{{ACTIONS_TABLE}}

Example:

```bash
{{SERVICE_SLUG}}-agent-connector --action {{FIRST_ACTION}} --params '{{FIRST_ACTION_EXAMPLE_PARAMS}}'
```

Output is a JSON envelope on stdout.

## Library

```ts
import { fetch, validActions } from "@narai/{{SERVICE_SLUG}}-agent-connector";
const result = await fetch("{{FIRST_ACTION}}", { /* params */ });
```

## What's not here

- {{READ_WRITE_NOTE}}
- No wiki, documentation, or diagramming — output is a pure JSON envelope.
- Credentials: use [`@narai/credential-providers`](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@narai/credential-providers) directly for backends other than `{{SERVICE_SLUG_UPPER}}_TOKEN`.

## Claude Code plugin

A ready-to-install Claude Code plugin lives at [`plugin/`](./plugin). It adds a `{{SERVICE_SLUG}}-agent` skill and a `/{{SERVICE_SLUG}}-agent <action> <params-json>` slash command, wrapping this connector. The plugin is excluded from the npm tarball via `.npmignore`.

